$ Oracle SQL: FLASHBACK DATABASE

`flashback database` rewinds a → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/database to
  • a given (past) point in time
  • an → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/transaction/SCN[SCN]
  • a → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/database/files/redo-log/sequence[log sequence] number
  • restore point

This command can be run from → development/databases/Oracle/tools/RMAN[RMAN] (prompt or `run` command)

sa:
  → development/databases/Oracle/SQL/statement/nouns/table/flashback[`flashback table`]

  → development/databases/Oracle/Features_Options_Management-Packs/Flashback
